This paper discusses the ability of models to extrapolate to examples outside the training space in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of capturing global structures, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions word embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
